    "department": "Supply Chain",
    "description": "Aescape is a New York–based technology company building the future of recovery. Through intelligent, precision bodywork, Aescape delivers personalized experiences that adapt to every body—turning recovery into a consistent, outcomes-driven practice so people can move better, recover faster, and feel their best every day.\n\nBy combining real-time body intelligence, advanced robotics, and proprietary software designed to improve with every session, Aescape transforms recovery from an occasional service into a scalable, measurable system—setting a new standard for modern wellness.\n\nAescape powers recovery across leading fitness, hospitality, and wellness environments and is backed by Valor Equity Partners, BroadLight Capital, and Mecha Ventures. For more information, visit www.aescape.com http://www.aescape.com.\n\n***This role is Hybrid from our NYC HQ***\n\nAescape is building the next generation of automated massage and wellness technology. As we expand our partner network, we are looking for a Manager, Partner Revenue Operations to own the business and financial workflows that support our partner ecosystem. This role will report to the SVP, Finance \u0026 Administration and manage the end-to-end business and financial lifecycle of partner transactions, including equipment sales, leasing payments, booking platform revenue settlements, revenue share agreements, and recurring service plans.\n\nYou will work cross-functionally with Finance, Sales, Partner Success, Operations, and Product to drive process excellence, system reliability, and scalable revenue operations.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO \n\n - inefficiencies, standardizing workflows and driving automation to improve speed and accuracy.\n\n - Own sales operations data integrity within Salesforce, establishing validation standards, audit controls, and governance processes to ensure all deal, contract, and partner data is accurate, complete, and consistently maintained.\n\n - Define and enforce clear handoff standards between Sales, Finance, and Operations at each stage of the revenue cycle to eliminate delays and errors.\n\n - In collaboration with the Finance team, ensure the billing and collections for equipment sales, lease payments, and service plans.\n\n - Oversee partner revenue share and booking platform settlements.\n\n - Monitor partner accounts and manage payment issues or disputes.\n\n - Improve business and financial workflow and identify opportunities to reduce revenue leakage and automate process.\n\n - Improve business and financial workflows and identify opportunities to reduce revenue leakage and automate processes.\n\n - Support finance and accounting teams with reporting and reconciliation.\n\n - Preferred: Experience with hardware, marketplace, or subscription business models.\n   \n   \n   \n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BRING\n\n - 5–8 years experience in sales operations, billing operations, or revenue operations, ideally in a B2B / B2C technology or hardware company.\n\n - Strong experience with sales operations, accounts receivable, invoicing, and collections\n\n - Hands-on experience with business and finance systems such as Salesforce, NetSuite, including CRM configuration, reporting, and data management.\n\n - Experience with data warehouse systems (eg., Snowflake) and familiarity with SQL for querying and validation data across systems.\n\n - Strong analytical and reconciliation skills.\n\n - Comfortable working cross-functionally in a fast-growing technology company.\n\n\nWHAT’S IN IT FOR YOU \n\n - Join a trailblazing tech company anticipated to transform the massage industry\n\n - The chance to make a difference with a product that empowers healthier and happier living\n\n - Team culture driven by passion, ambition, empowerment, inclusion, curiosity, and fun!\n\n - We’ll grow together – your personal and professional growth are equally important\n\n - An environment that empowers individuals, emboldens teams, and rewards achievement\n\n - Complimentary massages in our NY HQ and our Partner locations!\n\n - Medical, vision, and dental insurance covered by us\n\n - 401k with 4% company match\n\n - Flexible paid time off and a generous parental leave policy.\n\n - Working late? Dinner is on us.\n\n - Competitive pay + bonus + equity plan. The salary range for the role is $150,000-$180,000.\n\n\n\nBEGIN YOUR AESCAPE CAREER JOURNEY\n\nAt Aescape, we're on a mission to redefine self-care for a better world, and we're seeking trailblazers to join us on this journey. We're inspired by individuals who are passionate, driven, and eager to learn. We value diverse perspectives and resourceful, determined individuals who are committed to making a difference. At Aescape, we empower people to reach their full potential, just as our product empowers better living. If you're ready to innovate, create, and make a meaningful impact, we want you on our team.\n\nYOUR JOURNEY. YOUR AESCAPE.\n",
